<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idfe8a0e4b-9d45-11f0-a0db-bff75580f504" identifier="/us/usc/t24/s19"><num value="19">§ 19.</num><heading> Tubercular hospital at Fort Bayard</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">The hospital at Fort Bayard, New Mexico, for the treatment of tuberculosis, shall be opened to the treatment of the officers and men of the Navy and Marine Corps.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idfe8a0e4c-9d45-11f0-a0db-bff75580f504">(<ref href="/us/act/1907-03-02/ch2511">Mar. 2, 1907, ch. 2511</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/34/1172">34 Stat. 1172</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
</section>
